.TH "xen_xlate_map_ballooned_pages" 9 "xen_xlate_map_ballooned_pages" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
xen_xlate_map_ballooned_pages \- map a new set of ballooned pages
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" xen_xlate_map_ballooned_pages
.BI "(xen_pfn_t **gfns "  ","
.BI "void **virt "  ","
.BI "unsigned long nr_grant_frames "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "gfns" 12
returns the array of corresponding GFNs
.IP "virt" 12
returns the virtual address of the mapped region
.IP "nr_grant_frames" 12
number of GFNs
\fIreturn\fP 0 on success, error otherwise
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This allocates a set of ballooned pages and maps them into the
kernel's address space.
